Cell.Data: "The bow handle is engraved with a harrowing symbol, a seal of purity and zeal. Closer inspection reveals thirteen small markings on the bow wings, like if the previous owner was keeping track of a grim score. Whoever it was, its legacy is not meant to end here: time to start big game hunting and keep the death toll rolling."

Goremaker, Shard of the Red Mountain

During the war of the Primordials, the eternal lovers AnathÃ«a and Moros organized an assault on the Red Mountain, throne of Ashtaroth the lord of Flesh. Amidst the raging battle, the ground quaked as they realized the landscape itself was alive and about to engulf everything. They had no other choice than to obliterate the whole organic mountain to survive. This, could very well be one of its shards that survived through the eons.

The blacksmithing prodigy got to work, every night he would hammer hard at the anvil, shaping his lethal ambitions into an axe he would call âEdgyâ.\n\nRumor has it that Big Bill accidentally beheaded himself at night while training in the backyard. Bezeriel grew fond of observing a young beautiful maiden, incarnating all there is to love about youth. Taking the shape of a swann, he offered her this ring to show his admiration for her.\n\nShe smiled as she put the ring to her finger, but it was not to last: she soon withered in a matter of seconds, her lifeforce consumed and absorbed within the ringâs gem until it was full. No body was ever found for only dusts remained of her. Only the song of the âLost maidenâ that bards sing about, serves as a testimony of her doom.

"Isolated far east of the Four Realms of Men, the frontier city-state of Gomora is unfamously known for being the only settlement that openly welcomes evil worshippers. The champions in charge of keeping them in check are known as Arbiters, and receive such powerful onyx ring as a symbol of their absolute judgements."
